{{Messages|text=
:'''Aglaea:''' Not sure if you're into watching plays, (Trailblazer)
:'''Aglaea:''' A batch of new plays has been released, and I have reserved some seats for you
:{Choice} What plays?
::'''(Trailblazer):''' What plays?
::'''Aglaea:''' Well, let me introduce them to you
:{Choice} Not interested
::'''(Trailblazer):''' Not interested
::'''Aglaea:''' It won't hurt to hear about them
:{Choice} I wanna see Rosy Celestial Maiden
::'''(Trailblazer):''' Is Nikador Battles the Rosy Celestial Maiden on?
::'''Aglaea:''' Oh, such works are not uncommon
:'''Aglaea:''' Amphoreus' theater scene is vibrant, featuring an array of spectacular plays
:'''Aglaea:''' Such as the universally known and acclaimed classics, "The Aidonians," and "The Okheman Women"...
:'''Aglaea:''' Apart from serious works, some light-hearted, comedic plays are also quite popular
:'''Aglaea:''' For instance, this season includes titles like "Zagreus the Tyrant Falls in Love With Me," "I Turned into a Talking Dromas After A Nap," and "Fortress Kremnos"...
:'''Aglaea:''' I've heard these plays have a style quite distinct from the classics. Such a shame I haven't had the chance to see them yet
:{Choice} I really love these!
::'''(Trailblazer):''' I really love these kinds of shows!
:{Choice} Our tastes align!
::'''(Trailblazer):''' The tastes of the entire Cosmos align!
::'''Aglaea:''' Is that so? It could be an eventuality as art evolves
:{Choice} Everyone needs a break
::'''(Trailblazer):''' Everyone needs a break now and then
:'''Aglaea:''' These plays look like a ton of fun. It's no surprise they're so popular
:'''Aglaea:''' Let's chat about your thoughts once you've seen them
}}
